          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Blend lime juice, coconut milk, and cilantro stems. Set aside. Boil sweet potato 6 minutes. While cooking, sautee onions in 2 tbsp oil or butter over medium heat. Add in potatoes and cook 8 minutes. Add ginger, curry paste, and cayenne pepper and stir. Add in chickpeas and chicken (salt and pepper chicken beforehand) and cook 5 minutes. Add in coconut milk mixture and simmer until chicken is cooked through. Season with salt, add in jalapeno, and add 0.25 cup chopped cilantro. Mix in cauliflower rice."
        },
